^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Well, our auction was fine, just the contract turned out to be hopeless. Let us briefly discuss the 4th suit forcing by ira. He bid it first of all to establish a game forcing auction, while keeping the bidding lower. He was hoping I would show 3 card heart support, but I didn't. Once that doesn't happen, he cant really bid 2@H, because that would show a six card suit. So 2NT is probably best, because 3@D would be a diamond slam try. Now the other point is the play of the clubs. At trick two when pam gets in after winning with @DA, she should lead back remaining count, not the 7, either the six or the 4 to show she has more than a doubleton remaining. |
